  "On the y-axis (vertical)": "",
  "In the title of the graph": "",
  "On the x-axis (horizontal)": "",
  "In the legend of the graph": "",
  "By scientific convention, the independent variable is plotted on the x-axis (horizontal) and the dependent variable is plotted on the y-axis (vertical). This standard makes graphs easier to interpret.": "",
  "A student tests how the amount of sunlight affects plant growth. What is the independent variable?": "",
  "The height of the plant": "",
  "The type of soil used": "",
  "The amount of sunlight": "",
  "The amount of water given": "",
  "The amount of sunlight is the independent variable because it is what the student deliberately changes. The plant growth (height) is the dependent variable because it is what the student measures in response.": "",
  "A student tests how different temperatures affect the speed at which sugar dissolves. What is the dependent variable?": "",
  "The temperature of the water": "",
  "The type of sugar being used": "",
  "The amount of water in each cup": "",
  "The speed at which sugar dissolves": "",
